<br>
I dont expect anyone whose not in the guild to fully understand the tale behind her leaving the guild, lets just say, the members feel betrayed by her and feel that she has not only let them down, but has lied to them as well.<br>
<br>
This is just a warning, no-one should accept the help of a guild, that guilds resources, its members, their time, their effort, their willingness to help out, only to turn around and leave them without returning the favour.  When a guild commits to this kind of effort, on your part, and you accept that kind of help, you are imo, entering into a silent contract with that guild, to remain with that guild, at least until you have returned, in kind or in part, that which was given to you.<br>
<br>
You just dont accept help like that from a guild if you arent 100% sure that you wish to stay with that guild for the long run. <br>
<br>
I feel that she has used us to get where she wanted to be, and perhaps thats our fault for not seeing that side of her before we set our minds to getting her a cleric epic, but plz be aware, that if she has used us, dont think she may not use the next guild she joins.<br>
<br>
Maybe she wont, maybe shes learned her lesson, that no loot is worth friendship and respect, but that lesson, has come at a price, that price being the friendship and respect of many in Celtica.<br>
<br>
Many ppl use guilds to further themselves alone, they take from guilds without returning, no-one can force anyone to remain in a guild or to abide by the same moral codes or to understand or show the loyalty that others show them, for these ppl I have no respect, for her I have no respect.<br>
<br>
If you ever read this click chick, I used to think you were a really great person <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  so it hurts even more that you did, what you did.<br>
